Alembic migrations for Healthcare Policy & Claims Assistant.

Common commands (run from the `backend/` directory, or via
`docker compose exec backend ...`):

  alembic upgrade head               # apply all pending migrations
  alembic downgrade -1               # roll back the last migration
  alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe change"
  alembic current                    # show the current revision
  alembic history                    # list the revision graph

Notes
  * env.py reads DATABASE_URL from app settings, so you don't need to
    edit alembic.ini.
  * The pgvector extension is enabled by the initial migration; you don't
    need to install it manually inside the database.
